properties.areaDesc: Chesapeake Bay from Little Creek VA to Cape Henry VA including the Chesapeake Bay Bridge Tunnel
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 15 at 6:32PM EST until January 17 at 6:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 25 to 35 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt. Waves around 5 ft. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northwest winds 15 to 25 kt. Waves 3 to 4 ft.

* WHERE...Chesapeake Bay from Little Creek VA to Cape Henry VA
including the Chesapeake Bay Bridge Tunnel.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 PM Thursday to 6 AM EST
Friday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM to 6 PM EST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 6 PM EST THURSDAY... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THURSDAY TO 6 AM EST FRIDAY
